in python make a plot that compares two columns in a dataframe.
I can help you with that! Here's how you can do it:
1. Create two new columns in your dataframe, one for the x-axis and one for the y-axis.
2. Use the matplotlib library to create the plot.
3. Add a title to the plot that summarizes the main idea of the column comparison.
4. Include any relevant information you want to display.
5. Finally, use the seabed package to style your plot and make it look nice.
